cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.OH, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the performance analysis of a communication system affected by atmospheric turbulence and LOS blockage. Information theory is concerned with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information, which is relevant to this paper. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the performance of a free-space optical link, which is a type of wireless communication system. Networking and Internet Architecture is a relevant sub-category as it deals with the design and analysis of communication networks. 
3. cs.OH (Other Computer Science): This sub-category covers papers that do not fit into any of the other categories. This paper could potentially fall under this category as it deals with a specific application of communication systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the impact of atmospheric turbulence and LOS blockage on the performance of a communication system. Systems and Control is a relevant sub-category as it deals with the analysis and design of systems subject to uncertainty and disturbances. 
5. cs.PF (Performance): The paper is concerned with the performance analysis of a communication system under specific conditions. Performance is a relevant sub-category as it deals with the evaluation and optimization of system performance.
